      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. but i want to get even more specific with the tension. like, instead of just vague shadows, i want the protagonist to actually encounter some of the people. can you write a short passage where they walk past a group of local guys on a corner, and the way those guys look at them and move makes them feel like they're about to be victimized or something? i want to play into those common associations of these neighborhoods being high-crime or inherently aggressive. it'll make the reader feel that gut-level fear of being in the 'wrong' part of town.",
